  "stat_block": {
    "bulk": {
      "subtype": "bulk",
      "text": "L",
      "type": "stat_block_section",
      "value": null
    },
    "craft_requirements": "Supply a casting of a spell of the appropriate rank. The spell must have a casting time of [one-action] or [two-actions] , must have the polymorph trait, and must allow more than one choice of battle form.",
    "level": 6,
    "links": [
      {
        "alt": "polymorph",
        "aonid": 127,
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "polymorph",
        "type": "link"
      }
    ],
    "statistics": {
      "abilities": [
        {
          "ability_type": "offensive",
          "activation_types": [
            {
              "subtype": "activation_type",
              "type": "stat_block_section",
              "value": "cast a spell"
            }
          ],
          "effect": "You Cast the Spell, selecting two forms from among those you can normally choose. You gain the benefits of both forms. For example, if one form can breathe air and the other can breathe underwater, you can breathe in both situations. If there's overlap in abilities, you gain the better one. For instance, if both have a fly Speed, you get the higher one, and if both forms have claws, you gain only the claw Strike you prefer. The GM determines which abilities overlap and which are cumulative.",
          "frequency": "once per day, plus overcharge",
          "name": "Activate",
          "subtype": "activation",
          "type": "stat_block_section"
        }
      ],
      "subtype": "statistics",
      "type": "stat_block_section",
      "usage": {
        "subtype": "usage",
        "text": "held in 1 hand",
        "type": "stat_block_section"
      }
    },
    "subtype": "equipment",
    "text": "The grain of this simple wooden wand forms shifting images of sharp claws, snapping jaws, and countless creatures.",
    "traits": [
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 159,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "uncommon"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "f31704572455b8d77a8bd97c0045fde6",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "links": [
          {
            "alt": "Recall Knowledge",
            "aonid": 26,
            "game-obj": "Actions",
            "name": "Recall Knowledge",
            "type": "link"
          }
        ],
        "name": "Uncommon",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 11",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 11,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Something of uncommon rarity requires special training or comes from a particular culture or part of the world. Some character choices give access to uncommon options, and the GM can choose to allow access for anyone. Less is known about uncommon creatures than common creatures. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creature is increased by 2.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 103,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "15e2d048ce93e7b648064b09972535bc",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Magical",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 458,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Something with the magical trait is imbued with magical energies not tied to a specific tradition of magic. Some items or effects are closely tied to a particular tradition of magic. In these cases, the item has the arcane, divine, occult, or primal trait instead of the magical trait. Any of these traits indicate that the item is magical.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 127,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "69f30c8801710f12f6fbd5a2c7c0d91d",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "links": [
          {
            "alt": "counteract",
            "aonid": 371,
            "game-obj": "Rules",
            "name": "counteract",
            "type": "link"
          },
          {
            "alt": "magical",
            "aonid": 103,
            "game-obj": "Traits",
            "name": "magical",
            "type": "link"
          },
          {
            "alt": "manipulate",
            "aonid": 104,
            "game-obj": "Traits",
            "name": "manipulate",
            "type": "link"
          }
        ],
        "name": "Polymorph",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 301",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 301",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 301,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "These effects transform the target into a new form. A target can't be under the effect of more than one polymorph effect at a time. If it comes under the effect of a second polymorph effect, the second polymorph effect attempts to counteract the first. If it succeeds, it takes effect, and if it fails, the spell has no effect on that target. Any Strikes specifically granted by a polymorph effect are magical. Unless otherwise stated, polymorph spells don't allow the target to take on the appearance of a specific individual creature, but rather just a generic creature of a general type or ancestry.  \n  \n If you take on a battle form with a polymorph spell, the special statistics can be adjusted only by circumstance bonuses, status bonuses, and penalties. Unless otherwise noted, the battle form prevents you from casting spells, speaking, and using most manipulate actions that require hands. (If there's doubt about whether you can use an action, the GM decides.) Your gear is absorbed into you; the constant abilities of your gear still function, but you can't activate any items. If a polymorph effect causes you to increase in size, you must have space to expand into or the effect is disrupted.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 164,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "f7fe46b3a30bfb0e9bfbe655396afc22",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Wand",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 463",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 463",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 463,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "A wand contains a single spell which you can cast once per day.",
        "type": "trait"
      }
    ],
